'''1998年美国国会大厦枪击事件'''发生在1998年7月24日，导致两名[[美国国会警察|美国国会警察]]死亡。犯罪嫌疑人小拉塞尔·尤金·韦斯顿于当地时间15:40走进[[美国国会大厦|国会大厦]]开火，警探{{link-en|约翰·迈克尔·吉布森|John Gibson (police officer)}}和警官{{link-en|雅各布·切斯纳|Jacob Chestnut}}被其枪杀<ref name=CNN>{{cite news |url=http://www.cnn.com/US/9807/24/dc.shooting.03/ |title=2 dead, 2 hurt in U.S. Capitol shooting |publisher=CNN.com |accessdate=2013-05-28 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061029233005/http://www.cnn.com/US/9807/24/dc.shooting.03/ |archivedate=2006-10-29 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。切斯纳当天在[[乔治·华盛顿大学|乔治·华盛顿大学]]与世长辞，而吉布森则在{{link-en|华盛顿医疗中心|Washington Hospital Center}}进行手术时逝世。行凶者韦斯顿虽然被警方的回击打中，惟未能致其死命。其确切行凶动机不明，不过此人患有精神紊乱，并且对[[美國联邦政府|美國联邦政府]]有着强烈的不信任。之后他因[[精神分裂症|偏执型精神分裂症]]而被送入精神病院治疗，截止2013年5月仍然没有因為其行为而被送上法庭受审。

==枪击==
枪击当日，切斯纳和另一位警官获派操作位于国会大厦东门口的X光机和磁力仪，这里只对国会议员及其助手开放。吉布森警探负责保護几位重要代表，当时的[[联邦众议院|联邦众议院]]多数党领袖{{link-en|汤姆·德雷|Tom DeLay}}就在大门旁的办公室内。下午15:40，小拉塞尔·尤金·韦斯顿手持一把可装载6发子弹的.38口径[[史密斯威森|史密斯威森]][[左轮手枪|左轮手枪]]从门口走进国会大厦，这时切斯纳警官正在向一位游客和他的儿子指点方向，他的搭档也扶着另一位游客前往洗手间<ref name=buried>{{cite web | url = http://www.arlingtoncemetery.net/gib-ches.htm | title = Capitol Police Officers laid to rest in Arlington National Cemetery | publisher = Michael Robert Patterson | accessdate = 2013-05-28 | archive-date = 2020-11-16 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201116010803/http://www.arlingtoncemetery.net/gib-ches.htm | dead-url = no }}</ref>。韦斯顿绕过了[[金属探测器|金属探测器]]走进门内，切斯纳看到后，要求对方退回门外重新走过探测器<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/national/longterm/shooting/stories/main072598.htm | title = Gunman Shoots His Way Into Capitol; Two Officers Killed, Suspect Captured | publisher = Washingtonpost.com | accessdate = 2013-05-28 | date = 1999-01-30 | archive-date = 2021-01-18 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210118025358/https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/national/longterm/shooting/stories/main072598.htm | dead-url = no }}</ref>。在没有任何警告的情况下，韦斯顿突然在切斯纳背后掏出枪直接对准其后脑勺开枪。据证人报告，韦斯特接下来推开不远处的门走进了一组办公室，使用该组办公室的都是资深共和党议员，包括汤姆·德雷和之后将成为[[美国众议院议长|众议院议长]]的{{link-en|丹尼斯·哈斯特|Dennis Hastert}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.emergency.com/capshoot.htm |title=Attack on Capitol Hill |publisher=EmergencyNet News |accessdate=2013-05-28 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061208155832/http://emergency.com/capshoot.htm |archivedate=2006-12-08 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。

韦斯特走进德雷的办公室后又击中了身穿便衣的吉布森警探，尽管已身受重伤，但吉布森还是掏出枪向嫌犯回擊并打中了对方，韦斯特之后很快被捕<ref>{{cite news | url = http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?sec=health&res=9803E5DA1139F936A15754C0A96E958260 | title = Capitol Hill Slayings: The Overview; Gunman Invades Capitol, Killing 2 Guards | publisher = Newyorktimes.com | accessdate = 2013-05-28 | first = Francis X. | last = Clines | date = 1998-07-25 | archive-date = 2019-08-21 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190821151559/https://www.nytimes.com/1998/07/25/us/capitol-hill-slayings-the-overview-gunman-invades-capitol-killing-2-guards.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。一位女游客的脸部和肩膀被嫌犯打出的一颗子弹擦伤<ref>[http://www.findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4196/is_19980726/ai_n10434376 "Horrifying Capitol ordeal began with officer's execution"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4196/is_19980726/ai_n10434376 |date=20190821151551 }}. (1998-7-26). Milwaukee Journal Sentinel, The.</ref>，她在接受治疗后顺利出院。另一位国会警官道格拉斯·麦克米利安也被子弹打伤<ref name="Yehle 1, 18">{{cite news |first=Emily |last=Yehle |title= Weston Competency Hearing Set |url= |format= |work= Roll Call |publisher= Roll Call, Inc. |location= Washington, D.C. |id= |pages= 1, 18 |date= 2008-04-16 |accessdate=2013-05-28}}</ref>。之后将成为[[联邦参议院|联邦参议院]]多数党领袖的[[田纳西州|田纳西州]][[联邦参议员|参议员]]{{link-en|比尔·弗里斯特|Bill Frist}}事发前正在参议院楼层主持一次会议，他也是一位心脏外科医生。弗里斯特对枪手进行了急救，并将其送到了哥伦比亚特区总医院<ref name=CNN/>。

==枪击后==
[[Image:Capitol_Police_Honor_Guard_-_1998_shooting.jpg|thumb]]
这场袭击导致了切斯纳警官和吉布森警探丧生，两人的遗体随灵柩一起停放在国会大厦的圆形大厅接受瞻仰。这是首次有警察，并且也是首度有[[非裔美国人|非裔美国人]]获得这项荣誉<ref>{{cite web | url = http://thomas.loc.gov/cgi-bin/query/z?c105:H.R.4347: | title = Authorizing the use of the Rotunda of the Capitol... | publisher = United States Senate | accessdate = 2013-05-21 | archive-date = 2016-07-05 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160705000349/http://thomas.loc.gov/cgi-bin/query/z?c105:H.R.4347: | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

1999年，韦斯顿因被认为患有[[精神分裂症|精神分裂症]]并且擅自停药而不能接受审理<ref>{{cite news | url = http://edition.cnn.com/ALLPOLITICS/stories/1999/04/22/capitol.shooting/ | title = Weston found incompetent to stand trial for Capitol shooting | publisher = CNN.com | accessdate = 2013-05-28 | first = Terry | last = Frieden | archive-date = 2020-09-03 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200903090309/http://edition.cnn.com/ALLPOLITICS/stories/1999/04/22/capitol.shooting/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>。[[美国哥伦比亚特区地区法院|美国哥伦比亚特区地区法院]]的一位法官于2001年判决对其强制进行[[抗精神病药|抗精神病药物]]治疗，[[美国哥伦比亚特区巡回上诉法院|美国哥伦比亚特区巡回上诉法院]]维持了地区法院的原判<ref>{{cite web | url= http://nypress.com/capitol-shooter-russell-weston-three-years-later/ | title= Capitol Shooter Russell Weston, Three Years Later | publisher= New York Press | accessdate= 2013-05-28 | archive-date= 2016-03-05 | archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20160305021159/http://www.nypress.com/capitol-shooter-russell-weston-three-years-later/ | dead-url= no }}</ref>。到了2004年，虽然治疗一直在持续，但法院认定韦斯特的状况还是不能够受审，并暂时不对其发起刑事指控，但不排除将来再进行审判的可能。这起枪击案以前，韦斯特还曾威胁过[[美国总统|美国总统]]而引起过[[美国特勤局|美国特勤局]]的注意<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.cnn.com/US/9807/24/dc.shooting.04/ |title=Capitol shooting suspect was 'low-level threat' to Clinton |publisher=CNN.com |accessdate=2013-05-28 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050913025541/http://www.cnn.com/US/9807/24/dc.shooting.04/ |archivedate=2005-09-13 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。

枪击发生后，国会警察委员会建立了美国国会警察纪念基金，这是一个旨在为切斯纳和吉布森的家人提供经济支持的非盈利性组织<ref>{{cite web | url= http://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/2/1953 | title= U.S. Code Title 2, 1953 | publisher= Cornell Law School | accessdate= 2013-05-28 | archive-date= 2012-10-13 | archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20121013162344/http://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/2/1953 | dead-url= no }}</ref>。2005年11月，基金也开始对克里斯多夫·厄尼中士（Sgt. Christopher Eney）的家人提供支持，他是一位在1984年的一次训练事故中丧生的国会警察<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.house.gov/list/press/az01_renzi/flagfootball.html |title=Members, Capitol Police Square Off in 2006 "Longest Yard" Flag Football Game |publisher=Rep. Rick Renzi (AZ-01) |accessdate=2007-01-17 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070105104537/http://www.house.gov/list/press/az01_renzi/flagfootball.html |archivedate=2007-01-05 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。枪击事件也成为建立国会大厦游客中心的一个重要原因。哥伦比亚特区国会代表[[埃莉诺·福尔摩斯·诺顿|埃莉诺·福尔摩斯·诺顿]]为此提出了《1998年雅各布·约瑟夫·切斯纳-约翰·迈克尔·吉布森美国国会大厦游客中心法案》<ref>{{cite web | url = http://thomas.loc.gov/cgi-bin/query/z?c105:H.R.4347: | title = Jacob Joseph Chestnut-John Michael Gibson United States Capitol Visitor Center Act of 1998 (Introduced in House) | publisher = United States House of Representatives | accessdate = 2013-05-28 | archive-date = 2016-07-05 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160705000349/http://thomas.loc.gov/cgi-bin/query/z?c105:H.R.4347: | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/national/longterm/shooting/stories/security072698.htm | title = Attack Stirs Interest in Visitors Center | publisher = Washingtonpost.com | accessdate = 2013-05-28 | date = 1999-01-30 | archive-date = 2020-07-28 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200728105722/https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/national/longterm/shooting/stories/security072698.htm | dead-url = no }}</ref>。韦斯特所行经的门也改为切斯纳-吉布森纪念门来向两人致敬<ref>{{cite web | url = http://thomas.loc.gov/cgi-bin/query/z?c105:S.+Con.+Res.+113: | title = To rename the Document Door of the Capitol as the Chestnut-Gibson Memorial Door. (Introduced in Senate) | publisher = United States Senate | accessdate = 2013-05-28 | archive-date = 2019-08-21 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190821151552/https://www.congress.gov/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

2008年3月6日，韦斯顿提出动议要求对其精神状态召开一场听证会。这场听证会于5月6日举行，韦斯顿与他的公共辩护律师简·皮尔斯还有另外两位由他选择的证人，一位心理医生和一位职业康复专家4人一起在位于巴特纳的联邦惩教署通过电话会议与法官交流<ref>{{cite news |first=Emily |last=Yehle |title= Weston unlikely to ever be tried |url= |format= |work= Roll Call |publisher= Roll Call, Inc. |location= Washington, D.C. |id= |pages= 1, 16 |date= 2008-05-07 |accessdate=2013-05-28}}</ref>。联邦法官厄尔·布里特（Earl Britt）之后拒绝了韦斯顿从联邦机构释放的要求，认为他没有提供足够的证据证实自己不再需要被关押看管。听证会期间被告请来的心理医生霍利·罗杰斯表示，“有时间有些人虽然吃了药但就是没效果”，这也意味着韦斯顿还不能被释放。如果他将来获释，那么很有可能会被带到哥伦比亚特区因谋杀两位警察接受审判<ref name="Yehle 1, 18"/>。
